<br>
OTH, sometimes it's really hard to get a group.  Yesterday, I talked to 3 partials in Upper Guk -- one was Indigo Void (very nice RP, but they didn't like humans, so I stayed in character and didn't ask to group).  The other two just responded (more or less) &quot;we only want to group with ourselves&quot;.  Tried Sol-A.  Elven-blade group didn't even bother to answer my tell -- maybe they were all afk.  Other group was too high level.  Najena group claimed language barrier and full group (I've mastered all languages and there were 5 total in zone -- maybe someone off to sell).<br>
<br>
OTH, sometimes you zone in and are hit by a &quot;JOIN or DISBAND&quot; before you even speak.  It's definitely very weird for grouping.  I'd highly recommend a guild and I'm in the process of searching for one now.  Only progess so far is that I've crossed two off the list (yes, FV does have rude d00d guilds) and had some good brief casual contact with a few others.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=valquisssilverpalm>Valquiss Silverpalm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 144<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/13/02 11:24:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=208.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Finding Groups</span><hr size=1> A guild is a good way to go.  Barring that, keep a list of friends in your level range and ask then if they have groups you can join, and make sure to invite them in return when you can.  Get used to going where your friends are, rather than walking into a zone and assuming there is going to be a group at or near your favorite camp.  Pick up groups are not unknown, but they are the exception rather than the rule.  Make friends and keep them.  That's the best advise I know how to give.<br>
<br>
Valquiss<br>
<br>
P.S. Goodbye again Vallaelanan, one of my best and earliest friends from the battlefield.  I hope you'll be back, one day.<br>
